body:
There are no functions in std's [`Entry<K, V>` methods](https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/collections/hash_map/enum.Entry.html#methods) analogous to `or_insert_with` where the function argument returns a `Result<V, Error>` that insert the `Ok` case and return the `Err` value in the `Err` case.

This seems like a common enough use case to consider adding to std's Entry methods.

I created a new trait and impl in my code to add this function, below. If you think this is a reasonable function to add to the std, I am willing to create a PR with the new function, documentation, and tests, that will add this function to the Entry methods.

```
use std::collections::hash_map::Entry;

pub trait OrInsertWithResult<'a, V> {
    fn or_insert_with_result<E, F: FnOnce() -> Result<V, E>>(self, default: F)
        -> Result<&'a mut V, E>;
}

impl<'a, K, V> OrInsertWithResult<'a, V> for Entry<'a, K, V> {
    fn or_insert_with_result<E, F: FnOnce() -> Result<V, E>>(
        self,
        default: F,
    ) -> Result<&'a mut V, E> {
        match self {
            Entry::Vacant(v) => Ok(v.insert(default()?)),
            Entry::Occupied(o) => Ok(o.into_mut()),
        }
    }
}
```
cc @joshtriplett who graciously helped me write this bug report and code.
